name: onChange
desc:
Called whenever a Change occurs in any bloc
A change occurs when a new state is emitted.
onChange is called before a bloc's state has been updated.

name: onClose
desc:
Called whenever a Bloc is closed.
onClose is called just before the Bloc is closed
and indicates that the particular instance will no longer
emit new states.

name: onCreate
desc:
Called whenever a Bloc is instantiated.
In many cases, a cubit may be lazily instantiated and
onCreate can be used to observe exactly when the cubit
instance is created.

name: onError
desc: onError logs errors along with the stack trace for troubleshooting.

name: onEvent
desc:
Called whenever an event is added to any bloc with the given bloc
and event.

name: onTransition
desc:
onTransition logs each transition, showing the BLoC type, the previous
and next state types, and the event type.

name: inheritedMaybeOf
desc:
Obtain the nearest widget of the given type T,
which must be the type of a concrete InheritedWidget subclass,
and register this build context with that widget such that
when that widget changes (or a new widget of that type is introduced,
or the widget goes away), this build context is rebuilt so that it can
obtain new values from that widget.

name: WindowSize
desc:
Ð¡lass representing different window sizes, used for handling
various screen dimensions in a responsive manner.

name: aspectRatio
desc: The aspect ratio of this size.

name: bottomCenter
desc:
The offset to the center of the bottom edge of the rectangle described by
the given offset (which is interpreted as the top-left corner) and this
size.

name: bottomLeft
desc:
The offset to the intersection of the bottom and left edges of the
rectangle described by the given offset (which is interpreted as the
top-left corner) and this size.

name: bottomRight
desc:
The offset to the intersection of the bottom and right edges of the
rectangle described by the given offset (which is interpreted as the
top-left corner) and this size.

name: center
desc:
The offset to the point halfway between the left and right and the top and
bottom edges of the rectangle described by the given offset (which is
interpreted as the top-left corner) and this size.

name: centerLeft
desc:
The offset to the center of the left edge of the rectangle described by the
given offset (which is interpreted as the top-left corner) and this size.

name: centerRight
desc:
The offset to the center of the right edge of the rectangle described by the
given offset (which is interpreted as the top-left corner) and this size.

name: contains
desc:
Whether the point specified by the given offset (which is assumed to be
relative to the top left of the size) lies between the left and right and
the top and bottom edges of a rectangle of this size.

name: flipped
desc: A Size with the width and height swapped.

name: hashCode
desc: The hash code for this object.

name: height
desc: The vertical extent of this size.

name: isCompactFormat
desc: Returns true if the window is considered compact (width < minWidth of _WindowSizeCompact).

name: isEmpty
desc: Whether this size encloses a non-zero area.

name: isFinite
desc: Whether both components are finite (neither infinite nor NaN).

name: isInfinite
desc:
Returns true if either component is double.infinity, and false if both
are finite (or negative infinity, or NaN).

name: isLargeFormat
desc: Returns true if the window is considered large (width >= minWidth of _WindowSizeLarge).

name: isMediumFormat
desc: Returns true if the window is considered medium (width >= minWidth of _WindowSizeMedium).

name: longestSide
desc: The greater of the magnitudes of the width and the height.

name: map
desc: Maps the WindowSize to a value of type T.

name: maybeMap
desc: Lazy maps the WindowSize to a value of type T.

name: noSuchMethod
desc: Invoked when a nonexistent method or property is accessed.

name: operator %
desc: Modulo (remainder) operator.

name: operator *
desc: Multiplication operator.

name: operator +
desc: Binary addition operator for adding an Offset to a Size.

name: operator -
desc: Binary subtraction operator for Size.

name: operator /
desc: Division operator.

name: operator <
desc:
Less-than operator. Compares an Offset or Size to another Offset or
Size, and returns true if both the horizontal and vertical values of the
left-hand-side operand are smaller than the horizontal and vertical values
of the right-hand-side operand respectively. Returns false otherwise.

name: operator <=
desc:
Less-than-or-equal-to operator. Compares an Offset or Size to another
Offset or Size, and returns true if both the horizontal and vertical
values of the left-hand-side operand are smaller than or equal to the
horizontal and vertical values of the right-hand-side operand
respectively. Returns false otherwise.

name: operator ==
desc: Compares two Sizes for equality.

name: operator >
desc:
Greater-than operator. Compares an Offset or Size to another Offset
or Size, and returns true if both the horizontal and vertical values of
the left-hand-side operand are bigger than the horizontal and vertical
values of the right-hand-side operand respectively. Returns false
otherwise.

name: operator >=
desc:
Greater-than-or-equal-to operator. Compares an Offset or Size to
another Offset or Size, and returns true if both the horizontal and
vertical values of the left-hand-side operand are bigger than or equal to
the horizontal and vertical values of the right-hand-side operand
respectively. Returns false otherwise.

name: operator ~/
desc: Integer (truncating) division operator.

name: shortestSide
desc: The lesser of the magnitudes of the width and the height.

name: toString

name: topRight

described by the given offset (which is interpreted as the top-left corner)
and this size.

name: width
desc: The horizontal extent of this size.
